HEADWORD: Souvenir
<hw>Sou`ve*nir</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>souvenir</ets> to remember, fr. L. <ets>subvenire</ets> to come up,
come to mind; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>venire</ets> to come, akin to
E. <ets>come</ets>. <ets>See</ets> <er>Come</er>, and cf.
<er>Subvention</er>.]</ety> <def>That which serves as a reminder; a
remembrancer; a memento; a keepsake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

